# LAMMPS Input Script for Cyclohexane and Methane Mixture Simulation

units           real
atom_style      template

# Read in system configuration from data file
read_data       template-mix.data

# Define potential styles
pair_style      lj/cut 12.0
pair_modify     mix geometric tail yes
bond_style      harmonic
angle_style     harmonic
dihedral_style  harmonic

# Define interactions (example parameters, modify as needed)
pair_coeff      * * 0.0 0.0
bond_coeff      * 300.0 1.5
angle_coeff     * 50.0 109.5
dihedral_coeff  * 1.0 1 2

# Set up simulation box with periodic boundaries
boundary        p p p

# Define group for all atoms
group           all type *

# Define time integration and thermostat
timestep        1.0
fix             1 all nvt temp 300.0 300.0 100.0

# Output settings
thermo          100
thermo_style    custom step temp press pe ke etotal

# Run the simulation
run             2000

This script sets up a molecular dynamics simulation for a mixture of cyclohexane and methane using a template-based atom style. It applies the Lennard-Jones potential with a specified cutoff and employs harmonic potentials for bonded interactions. The Nos√©-Hoover thermostat manages temperature control, and periodic boundary conditions are applied to allow for a realistic simulation environment.